257
00:14:45,821 --> 00:14:48,281
Ms. Jo is the one we want to talk behind her back. Where is she?

258
00:14:48,721 --> 00:14:50,551
I don't know. We should go see her.

259
00:14:52,521 --> 00:14:54,481
There's Oh Dal Su.

260
00:14:55,021 --> 00:14:56,781
Just look at how big his head is.

261
00:14:57,181 --> 00:14:59,551
I feel so much better when I'm standing next to him.

262
00:15:00,551 --> 00:15:01,951
Dal Su.

263
00:15:01,951 --> 00:15:03,251
- Hello. - Hello.

264
00:15:03,251 --> 00:15:04,751
Hey, Kim Eun Gab.

265
00:15:04,951 --> 00:15:07,651
You were talking about my head again, weren't you?

266
00:15:07,721 --> 00:15:09,351
You really stand out.

267
00:15:10,621 --> 00:15:12,221
- Hey, Young Bin. - Hello.

268
00:15:12,721 --> 00:15:15,151
- We should do a movie together. - Of course.

269
00:15:15,321 --> 00:15:16,951
You really should.

270
00:15:17,051 --> 00:15:18,781
We want to sell 10 million tickets with you as a lucky charm.

271
00:15:18,881 --> 00:15:21,651
- Is your head the secret behind it? - Stop talking nonsense.

272
00:15:21,781 --> 00:15:23,451
I'm a bit busy right now. Sorry.

273
00:15:23,551 --> 00:15:25,981
- Enjoy the movie. - We will. Congratulations.

274
00:15:26,051 --> 00:15:27,681
You should drink coffee.

275
00:15:27,781 --> 00:15:29,421
- Okay. - Thank you.

276
00:15:29,421 --> 00:15:30,621
- Don't drink too much. - All right.

277
00:15:30,721 --> 00:15:32,781
Stay healthy. Don't get sick and live happily.

278
00:15:39,651 --> 00:15:41,081
That movie was so bad.

279
00:15:42,151 --> 00:15:43,951
I feel like I took a sleeping pill.

280
00:15:44,121 --> 00:15:46,051
Why did you have to snore?

281
00:15:46,181 --> 00:15:49,251
Was I not cursing? Even religious television is better than this.

282
00:15:49,381 --> 00:15:51,251
It really was painful to watch it until the end.

283
00:15:51,321 --> 00:15:52,721
I know, right? I'm worried for him.

284
00:15:52,881 --> 00:15:55,151
Did you get the ending?

285
00:15:55,451 --> 00:15:56,821
No.

286
00:15:57,681 --> 00:16:00,581
Cha Young Bin. Can you tell us what you thought about the movie?

287
00:16:00,681 --> 00:16:02,551
- Okay. - Let's get started.

288
00:16:02,881 --> 00:16:04,251
How did you like the movie?

289
00:16:04,351 --> 00:16:06,121
It was really good. I liked it.

290
00:16:06,221 --> 00:16:07,781
It was of good quality.

291
00:16:07,881 --> 00:16:11,351
The directing and acting were spotless.

292
00:16:11,621 --> 00:16:13,351
I'll recommend people around me to go watch this movie.

293
00:16:15,981 --> 00:16:17,421
- Is that good enough? - Thank you.

294
00:16:17,621 --> 00:16:19,121
- Okay. - Thank you.

295
00:16:19,121 --> 00:16:20,151
Thank you.

296
00:16:21,081 --> 00:16:23,321
You're so pretentious.

297
00:16:23,451 --> 00:16:26,521
You were right. Actors are not to be trusted.

298
00:16:26,651 --> 00:16:28,281
I hope Ms. Jo sees that.

299
00:16:28,381 --> 00:16:31,651
The thumbs up was too much.

300
00:16:31,651 --> 00:16:33,451
- That was... - Stop it now.

301
00:16:36,251 --> 00:16:38,121
It's Ms. Jo. Let's go talk to her.

302
00:16:42,051 --> 00:16:43,121
Ms. Jo.

303
00:16:44,551 --> 00:16:47,351
Is she ignoring me on purpose?

304
00:16:51,491 --> 00:16:52,621
Why isn't she...

305
00:16:58,991 --> 00:17:01,051
Ms. Jo.

306
00:17:03,781 --> 00:17:06,151
Come on. Hurry.

307
00:17:06,281 --> 00:17:07,281
Excuse me.

308
00:17:07,781 --> 00:17:09,451
- Ms. Jo. - Hey!

309
00:17:10,781 --> 00:17:12,991
She took off on us.

310
00:17:13,881 --> 00:17:15,551
Does she think we're stalkers?

311
00:17:16,781 --> 00:17:18,991
- It's Ms. Kang. - Is it her?

312
00:17:21,281 --> 00:17:23,321
- Why are you avoiding her? - Why are you?

313
00:17:24,051 --> 00:17:26,451
We didn't do anything wrong.

314
00:17:26,651 --> 00:17:27,681
Ji An is here, too.

315
00:17:27,951 --> 00:17:29,081
- You know Ji An? - No.

316
00:17:29,781 --> 00:17:32,021
- Who's that? - Should we go now?

317
00:17:32,081 --> 00:17:33,081
Let's go somewhere.

318
00:17:34,081 --> 00:17:36,381
There's no need for us to be shameful.

319
00:17:36,491 --> 00:17:38,521
Just be yourself.

320
00:17:38,621 --> 00:17:41,221
She's coming. Press the button.

321
00:17:41,751 --> 00:17:43,821
Face the restroom.

322
00:17:52,021 --> 00:17:54,021
You three make a good company.

323
00:17:54,351 --> 00:17:55,781
It's nice.

324
00:17:55,851 --> 00:17:58,151
You're here for the movie premier, too?

325
00:18:00,781 --> 00:18:03,521
- Hello, Mr. Kim. - Long time no see, Ji An.

326
00:18:03,751 --> 00:18:05,721
- Hello, you two. - Hello.

327
00:18:07,881 --> 00:18:09,621
What a boring movie.

328
00:18:10,251 --> 00:18:12,651
What a lame day this is.

329
00:18:12,721 --> 00:18:15,181
First the movie, and now this.

330
00:18:16,021 --> 00:18:17,021
Mom.

331
00:18:17,621 --> 00:18:19,621
- Aren't you coming? - We're expecting company.

332
00:18:19,721 --> 00:18:20,851
Go on up.

333
00:18:21,451 --> 00:18:23,121
Of course, you are.

334
00:18:23,851 --> 00:18:25,151
Are you expecting ghosts?

335
00:18:25,491 --> 00:18:27,991
You certainly feel like one. Go on up.

336
00:18:29,951 --> 00:18:32,051
Right. I wish you a long and happy life, too.

337
00:18:35,021 --> 00:18:36,081
Call me.

338
00:18:37,551 --> 00:18:38,581
What was that?

339
00:18:39,151 --> 00:18:40,551
- What was that just now? - Nothing.

340
00:18:40,921 --> 00:18:42,721
She's so strange. Why would she...

341
00:18:42,821 --> 00:18:44,751
What's wrong with her?

342
00:18:45,751 --> 00:18:47,551
- Is something going on? - No.

343
00:18:47,821 --> 00:18:50,651
She's fierce just like her mother. Get yourself together.

344
00:18:51,621 --> 00:18:53,381
Why isn't the elevator coming down?

345
00:18:53,621 --> 00:18:54,651
Why would she do that?

346
00:18:56,491 --> 00:18:58,351
You looked like you were avoiding me on purpose.

347
00:18:58,681 --> 00:19:00,421
Why would I? I didn't see you.

348
00:19:00,881 --> 00:19:03,321
You saw me after the premier.

349
00:19:03,721 --> 00:19:04,951
We were chasing you down.

350
00:19:05,621 --> 00:19:08,221
- I said I didn't see you. - Fine. I understand.

351
00:19:09,881 --> 00:19:11,521
Young Bin was there yesterday.

352
00:19:12,181 --> 00:19:13,681
He did an interview promoting the movie.

353
00:19:13,821 --> 00:19:14,821
So?

354
00:19:15,451 --> 00:19:18,221
He's doing it on purpose because he feels sorry to you.

355
00:19:18,821 --> 00:19:20,721
There's no need for that. It's over between us.

356
00:19:21,051 --> 00:19:22,721
How is it over?

357
00:19:23,221 --> 00:19:25,451
Even with a couple breaks up, they meet once for the last time.

358
00:19:26,421 --> 00:19:27,421
Are you...

359
00:19:27,921 --> 00:19:29,951
looking into the casting for "Lim Hwa Su"?

360
00:19:30,021 --> 00:19:31,281
Yes, of course.

361
00:19:32,221 --> 00:19:34,721
I've been looking into it as well, but there wasn't anyone available.

362
00:19:34,721 --> 00:19:35,881
You couldn't find anyone, could you?

363
00:19:36,251 --> 00:19:39,491
Song Joong Ki, Lee Min Ho, Kim Soo Hyun are all busy.

364
00:19:39,881 --> 00:19:41,251
It's an on-going process.

365
00:19:41,881 --> 00:19:45,821
Ms. Jo. Can you at least see Young Bin for one last time?

366
00:19:46,651 --> 00:19:49,051
What's so hard about that? Don't bring emotions to business.

367
00:19:49,151 --> 00:19:50,581
You know better than that.

368
00:19:50,681 --> 00:19:52,751
He was the one who got emotional first.

369
00:19:53,351 --> 00:19:56,121
Please. Give him one meeting.

370
00:19:56,521 --> 00:19:57,951
If you do that,

371
00:19:58,581 --> 00:20:00,781
ask me for any favor and I'll deliver.

372
00:20:01,021 --> 00:20:02,021
Is that right?

373
00:20:02,781 --> 00:20:04,751
Lee El is with you, right?

374
00:20:05,251 --> 00:20:07,351
That's right. She's part of our agency.

375
00:20:08,821 --> 00:20:11,491
I'm doing a new movie soon. I want her on it.

376
00:20:11,651 --> 00:20:12,751
Do that for me.

377
00:20:14,081 --> 00:20:16,951
Then I'll think about it.

378
00:20:24,181 --> 00:20:26,451
Stop reading and start talking.

379
00:20:27,251 --> 00:20:28,491
What do you think?

380
00:20:31,381 --> 00:20:34,051
I think it could work.

381
00:20:34,651 --> 00:20:37,151
The investors like throwing away their money.

382
00:20:37,621 --> 00:20:38,651
To be honest,

383
00:20:39,451 --> 00:20:40,781
I wouldn't invest in something like this.

384
00:20:40,921 --> 00:20:42,991
I don't really like the script, either.

385
00:20:43,351 --> 00:20:45,451
And the female role has such a small part.

386
00:20:45,581 --> 00:20:48,621
This is what she gave to Lee El.

387
00:20:49,151 --> 00:20:50,821
She's going to play such a petty role.

388
00:20:52,491 --> 00:20:54,851
We're making a deal, right?

389
00:20:55,421 --> 00:20:56,421
We are.

390
00:20:56,521 --> 00:21:00,491
If we give her Lee El, she'll think positively about Young Bin.

391
00:21:00,491 --> 00:21:02,181
It's a good deal for her.

392
00:21:03,181 --> 00:21:05,951
She doesn't want a rookie, but a top actress wouldn't be willing.

393
00:21:05,991 --> 00:21:09,181
She's going to get what she wants.

394
00:21:10,991 --> 00:21:14,551
If Lee El does this,

395
00:21:15,451 --> 00:21:17,221
will she let Young Bin do "Lim Hwa Su"?

396
00:21:18,521 --> 00:21:21,551
If she has a conscience, she'll at least meet him.

397
00:21:22,021 --> 00:21:23,781
She probably will.

398
00:21:23,881 --> 00:21:25,081
- Right. - By the way,

399
00:21:26,081 --> 00:21:28,781
we're almost handing over Lee El at the wholesale price.

400
00:21:28,881 --> 00:21:32,121
This thing we're doing...

401
00:21:32,181 --> 00:21:34,321
- I know. - This isn't our style.

402
00:21:34,421 --> 00:21:36,921
This isn't the way we do things.

403
00:21:37,081 --> 00:21:38,221
Gosh, you scared me.

404
00:21:39,781 --> 00:21:41,481
You scared me to death.

405
00:21:41,821 --> 00:21:43,451
What's the special occasion? You're never on time.

406
00:21:43,951 --> 00:21:46,021
I made him wait for too long the other day.

407
00:21:46,751 --> 00:21:49,221
Do you want to have a meal with me? I'm feeling hungry.

408
00:21:50,651 --> 00:21:52,551
Okay. Let's do that.

409
00:21:55,751 --> 00:21:57,681
Why didn't she ask me?

410
00:21:59,521 --> 00:22:01,181
How are we going to do this?

411
00:22:01,321 --> 00:22:02,881
Are you going to make her do this?

412
00:22:07,221 --> 00:22:10,181
We could pretend to answer to her demands...

413
00:22:10,481 --> 00:22:13,421
and get Young Bin a meeting for "Lim Hwa Su" first.

414
00:22:14,121 --> 00:22:15,821
You're good at things like that, right?

415
00:22:18,181 --> 00:22:22,421
That's what I was going to do, but I don't like it coming from you.

416
00:22:23,181 --> 00:22:25,551
Well, you're the expert.

417
00:22:26,351 --> 00:22:30,081
I'll just inform her that there's an opening.

418
00:22:30,821 --> 00:22:31,821
Okay.

419
00:22:33,081 --> 00:22:34,281
Go now.

420
00:22:41,221 --> 00:22:43,151
Is he becoming more like me or what?

421
00:22:43,951 --> 00:22:45,121
Where was I?

422
00:22:54,551 --> 00:22:55,551
That's not it.

423
00:22:56,381 --> 00:22:57,381
How's it coming along?

424
00:22:59,381 --> 00:23:01,281
I don't remember anything. I should look it up.

425
00:23:01,821 --> 00:23:04,081
Why do you want me to do Sugar Boys dance?

426
00:23:04,151 --> 00:23:07,321
I think it'll be funny. Going old-school is the trend.

427
00:23:07,981 --> 00:23:09,021
I guess so.

428
00:23:17,351 --> 00:23:18,921
What are you doing here?

429
00:23:19,021 --> 00:23:20,221
I came to see you.

430
00:23:21,181 --> 00:23:23,051
- You still can't dance, can you? - It's Lee Joo Yeon.

431
00:23:23,221 --> 00:23:26,051
You were the worst dancer in your group.

432
00:23:26,121 --> 00:23:28,551
What are you talking about? I was the lead dancer.

433
00:23:28,651 --> 00:23:30,121
You should go now. I have to practice.

434
00:23:30,581 --> 00:23:31,721
I was about to.

435
00:23:32,851 --> 00:23:33,881
By the way,

436
00:23:34,621 --> 00:23:36,221
what are you doing this evening?

437
00:23:36,921 --> 00:23:38,021
I'll be home.

438
00:23:38,281 --> 00:23:41,581
I'm going to meditate and study humanism.

439
00:23:41,881 --> 00:23:43,521
I'm free tonight.

440
00:23:44,251 --> 00:23:45,821
I'm finally having a day off.

441
00:23:47,351 --> 00:23:48,881
Do you want to have dinner with me?

442
00:23:49,381 --> 00:23:50,951
I told you. I have to meditate and...

443
00:23:53,721 --> 00:23:55,781
Are you going to take me somewhere fancy?

444
00:23:55,981 --> 00:23:57,281
Of course.

445
00:23:58,751 --> 00:24:03,921
You don't have a date with your girlfriend, do you?

446
00:24:04,351 --> 00:24:06,181
A girlfriend? I don't have one.

447
00:24:07,421 --> 00:24:09,221
I'll give you a call later.

448
00:24:10,021 --> 00:24:12,581
- But you don't have my number. - Yes, I do.

449
00:24:17,551 --> 00:24:20,051
Joon, are you friends with Lee Joo Yeon?

450
00:24:20,221 --> 00:24:22,751
Not at all. I don't know why she's acting friendly all of a sudden.

451
00:24:22,851 --> 00:24:25,221
Maybe she likes you.

452
00:24:25,721 --> 00:24:28,021
What? Don't be ridiculous.

453
00:24:28,181 --> 00:24:29,751
I'm probably the last person she cares about.

454
00:24:31,281 --> 00:24:34,181
She used to look down on me in the old days.

455
00:24:34,581 --> 00:24:37,251
That's true. There's no way Lee Joo Yeon is into you.

456
00:24:41,551 --> 00:24:43,621
So why is she acting friendly? Does she have a favor to ask?

457
00:24:45,521 --> 00:24:46,621
Is it because of Young Bin?

458
00:25:23,821 --> 00:25:26,321
- Ms. Skateboard? - My name is Min Ah.

459
00:25:27,521 --> 00:25:28,621
I wasn't asking.

460
00:25:32,321 --> 00:25:34,181
Did you not come with Young Bin today?

461
00:25:34,521 --> 00:25:35,751
I came alone. Why?

462
00:25:35,851 --> 00:25:39,021
I've been waiting since morning. That's too bad.

463
00:25:39,181 --> 00:25:41,581
Since morning? Don't you work? Don't you go to school?

464
00:25:41,851 --> 00:25:42,921
I'm a student on leave.

465
00:25:43,281 --> 00:25:45,121
So that's why you're out here every day.

466
00:25:46,381 --> 00:25:49,081
What do you do, Mister? Are you unemployed?

467
00:25:49,621 --> 00:25:51,851
I'm not "Mister", but I am unemployed.

468
00:25:52,151 --> 00:25:54,421
No wonder I always see you around.

469
00:26:01,751 --> 00:26:02,821
What's wrong?

470
00:26:03,781 --> 00:26:04,821
I'm hungry.

471
00:26:20,821 --> 00:26:21,821
I mean...

472
00:26:22,221 --> 00:26:24,951
What are you doing in Seoul if you live in Daejeon? Did you run away?

473
00:26:26,681 --> 00:26:27,951
I'm a grown-up.

474
00:26:28,651 --> 00:26:29,881
I just left.

475
00:26:30,821 --> 00:26:33,951
I was sick of working part-time and the nagging from my parents.

476
00:26:34,951 --> 00:26:36,081
I hate my life.

477
00:26:36,821 --> 00:26:39,421
- So you did run away from home. - I'm on a trip.

478
00:26:41,521 --> 00:26:43,351
Thanks for the food.

479
00:26:45,121 --> 00:26:46,521
I can buy you food,

480
00:26:46,521 --> 00:26:49,721
but why did you have to get the most expensive lunch box?

481
00:26:50,621 --> 00:26:51,951
That's why I'm thanking you.

482
00:26:54,121 --> 00:26:56,751
I sleep in my friend's dorm room,

483
00:26:57,551 --> 00:26:59,881
but I ran out of money to buy food.

484
00:27:00,621 --> 00:27:03,121
Then go home. Or you could go back to school.

485
00:27:03,221 --> 00:27:05,321
The tuition is so expensive, though.

486
00:27:05,881 --> 00:27:07,451
It's not like there's a guarantee I'll get a job after I graduate.

487
00:27:08,381 --> 00:27:09,381
Don't you have anything that you want to do?

488
00:27:12,381 --> 00:27:16,051
I don't know. I'd like to win the lottery.

489
00:27:17,081 --> 00:27:18,551
Gosh.

490
00:27:21,821 --> 00:27:23,181
Do you think I'm pathetic?

491
00:27:24,021 --> 00:27:26,281
No. It's just that you're so much like me.

492
00:27:26,651 --> 00:27:28,521
We're both freeloaders, unemployed, and hopeless.

493
00:27:29,381 --> 00:27:30,381
That makes us buddies.

494
00:27:31,051 --> 00:27:32,051
Right.

495
00:27:35,051 --> 00:27:37,281
What's that alarm for? Do you have an appointment?

496
00:27:37,481 --> 00:27:40,651
No, I set the alarm for a cartoon show, "Adventure Time".

497
00:27:41,451 --> 00:27:42,951
That's my favorite show.

498
00:27:43,421 --> 00:27:45,851
- Jack the dog - Finn the human

499
00:27:47,821 --> 00:27:49,851
Do you watch "K-On!"?

500
00:27:50,651 --> 00:27:52,751
I've seen up until season 2. I've seen the movie, too.

501
00:27:52,851 --> 00:27:54,821
You're a nerd.

502
00:27:55,051 --> 00:27:57,551
Right. Is that bad?

503
00:27:57,751 --> 00:28:00,721
No, not all the time.

504
00:28:07,851 --> 00:28:09,481
Hello? Hey, Joon.

505
00:28:09,781 --> 00:28:12,151
- Let's eat outside tonight. - What are you talking about?

506
00:28:12,621 --> 00:28:14,521
Joo Yeon says she wants to buy me dinner.

507
00:28:14,821 --> 00:28:15,851
Then have dinner with her.

508
00:28:15,881 --> 00:28:17,751
Why would I want to have dinner alone with her?

509
00:28:18,221 --> 00:28:20,421
I'll order everything and make her pay a big bill.

510
00:28:22,221 --> 00:28:24,181
What's wrong with you? You're so childish.

511
00:28:24,981 --> 00:28:27,121
Fine, I'll come.

512
00:28:27,781 --> 00:28:29,081
I promise. Bye.

513
00:28:31,921 --> 00:28:34,521
Are you going somewhere? Are you going to see Cha Young Bin?

514
00:28:35,951 --> 00:28:39,451
He's a Cha, too. But he's a different Cha.

515
00:28:41,181 --> 00:28:44,051
- He wants to have dinner together. - Can I tag along?

516
00:28:44,881 --> 00:28:47,421
We're not that close. Let's not cross the line here.

517
00:28:47,521 --> 00:28:48,821
