No, the other way.

781
00:42:26,281 --> 00:42:28,591
That was good, but let's try one more time. Go the other way.

782
00:42:29,551 --> 00:42:30,551
One, two.

783
00:42:35,821 --> 00:42:38,781
You're rolling off beat. It has to be accurate.

784
00:42:39,451 --> 00:42:41,421
Go a little more. No, the other way.

785
00:42:41,521 --> 00:42:43,981
One more time. Face down.

786
00:42:45,351 --> 00:42:47,481
- One, two. Do it again. - That's what I want.

787
00:42:49,821 --> 00:42:52,581
- A little bit more. - Good work, Joon.

788
00:42:54,151 --> 00:42:56,721
Gosh, be careful with it. Put it away, please.

789
00:42:57,251 --> 00:42:58,621
What is this, seriously?

790
00:42:59,421 --> 00:43:02,221
Joon, you at least get to talk.

791
00:43:02,321 --> 00:43:03,681
You say that because you're not doing it.

792
00:43:03,781 --> 00:43:06,521
Stop whining already. You're shooting a commercial.

793
00:43:06,621 --> 00:43:09,051
How can Joo Yeon recommend me for something like this?

794
00:43:09,151 --> 00:43:10,751
Gosh, you're being so ungrateful.

795
00:43:10,981 --> 00:43:12,321
My pride is crushed.

796
00:43:13,051 --> 00:43:14,621
She's the main model when I'm...

797
00:43:15,281 --> 00:43:16,281
the dice.

798
00:43:16,281 --> 00:43:18,421
Joon, the dice is the most important role.

799
00:43:18,621 --> 00:43:20,381
Gosh, you're so insecure.

800
00:43:20,881 --> 00:43:23,521
Why do you keep taking her side?

801
00:43:24,181 --> 00:43:27,781
Have you become best friends with her after the barbecue? You jerk.

802
00:43:28,021 --> 00:43:30,551
Watch your tongue, seriously. I'll leave if you keep this up.

803
00:43:30,751 --> 00:43:32,251
Go. Get lost.

804
00:43:32,381 --> 00:43:34,251
Go home before I lose it on you. I don't need you.

805
00:43:36,621 --> 00:43:38,051
She has always been like this.

806
00:43:38,751 --> 00:43:41,051
Ever since they won the first place on "Music Top 10", they started...

807
00:43:41,181 --> 00:43:43,221
belittling us for only doing variety shows. They used to laugh at us.

808
00:43:43,721 --> 00:43:46,051
They even ignored us when we said hi to them at the agency.

809
00:43:46,151 --> 00:43:48,351
Gosh, how obnoxious. That witch.

810
00:43:48,981 --> 00:43:51,981
Yes, you're absolutely right. I'll get going, then.

811
00:43:53,151 --> 00:43:54,221
I should get out of here.

812
00:43:58,381 --> 00:44:00,751
I'll just come back another time.

813
00:44:05,921 --> 00:44:08,581
She... She heard everything.

814
00:44:08,681 --> 00:44:10,321
She heard... She heard everything.

815
00:44:11,851 --> 00:44:13,481
She heard every single thing you said.

816
00:45:14,751 --> 00:45:15,751
So?

817
00:45:16,751 --> 00:45:18,621
Did you date my friend, Sun Young, secretly?

818
00:45:20,621 --> 00:45:22,051
No, I just slept with her.

819
00:45:24,681 --> 00:45:25,681
- There's more, right? - Goodness.

820
00:45:27,581 --> 00:45:29,181
Gosh, what was her name?

821
00:45:30,651 --> 00:45:31,681
Right, Ji Hye.

822
00:45:33,321 --> 00:45:34,321
Is that it?

823
00:45:35,821 --> 00:45:36,821
What about Ah Jeong?

824
00:45:37,881 --> 00:45:39,251
Nothing happened with her, right?

825
00:45:40,251 --> 00:45:43,481
- She's my best friend. - What do you want from me?

826
00:45:48,921 --> 00:45:50,381
Goodness gracious. How dare you?

827
00:45:50,781 --> 00:45:51,781
Cut.

828
00:45:55,821 --> 00:45:57,051
All right, let's try it again.

829
00:46:00,421 --> 00:46:01,421
Sure, let's do it.

830
00:46:03,081 --> 00:46:04,081
Ready,

831
00:46:05,081 --> 00:46:06,081
action!

832
00:46:19,081 --> 00:46:20,351
- Why was it... - Guys.

833
00:46:21,051 --> 00:46:22,981
Thanks for everything. Great work, today.

834
00:46:23,751 --> 00:46:25,381
I must say, she slapped me so hard.

835
00:46:25,451 --> 00:46:26,851
I'm sorry.

836
00:46:27,021 --> 00:46:28,721
I don't mean to be rude,

837
00:46:29,151 --> 00:46:30,921
but that was different from the script.

838
00:46:31,451 --> 00:46:32,951
Getting slapped in the face wasn't in the script.

839
00:46:33,051 --> 00:46:35,151
Gosh. Go easy on me, please.

840
00:46:35,251 --> 00:46:37,821
I revised it a little at the last minute to make it more fun.

841
00:46:37,921 --> 00:46:39,421
It's okay. I had fun.

842
00:46:39,551 --> 00:46:41,051
Eun Gab won't badmouth me, will he?

843
00:46:41,521 --> 00:46:43,921
I'll put in a good word for you when I speak to Ms. Jo.

844
00:46:46,321 --> 00:46:47,381
Speak of the devil.

845
00:46:47,681 --> 00:46:48,751
Bye.

846
00:46:49,751 --> 00:46:50,751
Yes, Ms. Jo.

847
00:46:51,551 --> 00:46:54,351
Did you know? We shot the scene with Young Bin today.

848
00:46:54,351 --> 00:46:55,421
Hey, it's okay.

849
00:46:56,751 --> 00:46:58,451
That was my first ever loser role, but it was fun.

850
00:46:58,581 --> 00:47:01,151
A loser played a loser. You did a good job.

851
00:47:02,251 --> 00:47:03,251
Let's go.

852
00:47:04,251 --> 00:47:06,781
- Hello? - Where are you now?

853
00:47:07,481 --> 00:47:09,221
Me? I'm in front of my place.

854
00:47:09,751 --> 00:47:10,851
Where exactly?

855
00:47:14,251 --> 00:47:15,881
- I'm here. - Gosh.

856
00:47:21,421 --> 00:47:23,081
Are you waiting for Young Bin again?

857
00:47:23,381 --> 00:47:24,881
No, not today. I'm just...

858
00:47:27,781 --> 00:47:28,821
I just wanted to come here.

859
00:47:30,721 --> 00:47:32,121
I guess you're going home.

860
00:47:32,251 --> 00:47:34,351
Yes. I packed up all of my stuff.

861
00:47:35,051 --> 00:47:36,921
I came just in case, but I'm so lucky.

862
00:47:43,281 --> 00:47:45,281
I'm actually here to see you.

863
00:47:47,221 --> 00:47:48,851
Me... Me?

864
00:47:53,381 --> 00:47:55,181
I'm embarrassed that I said it.

865
00:48:03,621 --> 00:48:05,721
What's wrong? Are you hungry again?

866
00:48:06,951 --> 00:48:08,251
No, my stomach is a little upset.

867
00:48:09,421 --> 00:48:11,581
Can I use your bathroom?

868
00:48:11,981 --> 00:48:14,251
Sure. You shouldn't hold it in if it's number two.

869
00:48:14,921 --> 00:48:16,051
- Thank you. - Let's go.

870
00:48:19,451 --> 00:48:21,521
Here. Pick one.

871
00:48:21,851 --> 00:48:23,081
I'll give it to you as a souvenir.

872
00:48:23,751 --> 00:48:26,121
My goodness. You seriously rock.

873
00:48:28,981 --> 00:48:30,051
I'll be right back.

874
00:48:31,081 --> 00:48:33,221
- You can only pick one, okay? - All right.

875
00:48:34,521 --> 00:48:36,051
Just so you know, the gray one is the cheapest.

876
00:48:39,881 --> 00:48:41,751
Just apologize to her. What else can you say?

877
00:48:41,981 --> 00:48:43,851
I can't. I'm too embarrassed!

878
00:48:44,681 --> 00:48:47,281
You shouldn't blame it on her no matter how bad the situation is.

879
00:48:47,551 --> 00:48:50,721
Also, I don't think you realize that Joo Yeon likes you.

880
00:48:51,021 --> 00:48:52,521
You're at it again.

881
00:48:53,221 --> 00:48:54,921
You're basically kicking your luck away.

882
00:48:54,921 --> 00:48:56,551
I clearly told you. You deal with the rest.

883
00:48:57,351 --> 00:48:58,451
Did you pick one?

884
00:49:02,381 --> 00:49:05,481
What's she doing? Is she out of her mind?

885
00:49:06,551 --> 00:49:07,551
Hey.

886
00:49:12,421 --> 00:49:13,451
What on earth are you doing here?

887
00:49:14,151 --> 00:49:16,551
I just wanted to lie down on Cha Young Bin's bed.

888
00:49:17,051 --> 00:49:18,621
Stop talking nonsense and just get up.

889
00:49:19,181 --> 00:49:20,951
Just a little more. Just one more minute.

890
00:49:21,151 --> 00:49:22,981
Do you think that this is a sauna or what?

891
00:49:23,221 --> 00:49:25,851
- Get up already. - Gosh, just a little more.

892
00:49:25,881 --> 00:49:27,881
- Why are you so strong? - Please, please...

893
00:49:37,051 --> 00:49:38,121
Where am I right now?

894
00:49:46,181 --> 00:49:47,181
Well...

895
00:49:47,551 --> 00:49:50,981
That wasn't... That wasn't intentional.

896
00:49:51,651 --> 00:49:52,721
I should get up now.

897
00:49:55,921 --> 00:49:59,881
I wasn't going to give you the shirt if you stayed like that for longer.

898
00:49:59,981 --> 00:50:01,881
What am I saying? I'm not making much sense.

899
00:50:02,781 --> 00:50:03,821
I'm sorry.

900
00:50:04,081 --> 00:50:05,921
No, I'm sorry. Oh, I can take care of this.

901
00:50:16,951 --> 00:50:19,151
Can we talk?

902
00:50:26,421 --> 00:50:28,221
Go ahead.

903
00:50:28,821 --> 00:50:30,251
You heard everything I said, right?

904
00:50:32,951 --> 00:50:34,021
I'm sorry.

905
00:50:37,851 --> 00:50:38,851
Well...

906
00:50:42,121 --> 00:50:43,321
Your band...

907
00:50:44,251 --> 00:50:45,981
was very popular.

908
00:50:48,321 --> 00:50:49,821
My band failed and broke up.

909
00:50:52,981 --> 00:50:55,121
Whenever I saw you,

910
00:50:56,651 --> 00:50:59,381
I felt jealous. That's probably why.

911
00:51:02,881 --> 00:51:04,481
It was petty of me.

912
00:51:07,021 --> 00:51:08,021
I'm sorry.

913
00:51:12,951 --> 00:51:13,951
I'm sorry.

914
00:51:14,651 --> 00:51:15,751
Was it funny?

915
00:51:16,181 --> 00:51:19,221
It's just that outfit. It looks silly.

916
00:51:19,521 --> 00:51:22,751
You talked so seriously in that outfit.

917
00:51:25,921 --> 00:51:27,021
All right. Laugh.

918
00:51:29,151 --> 00:51:32,351
Please laugh as much as you want and accept my apology.

919
00:51:33,351 --> 00:51:34,421
It's okay.

920
00:51:35,121 --> 00:51:38,981
I was young back then. I did many bad things to people around me.

921
00:51:40,251 --> 00:51:42,451
Our hectic schedule made me tired,

922
00:51:42,551 --> 00:51:44,421
and my agency didn't give me much freedom.

923
00:51:45,421 --> 00:51:46,921
I couldn't look around myself.

924
00:51:48,151 --> 00:51:51,381
I was a weird kid.

925
00:51:52,751 --> 00:51:53,781
You think so?

926
00:51:54,821 --> 00:51:55,821
Also,

927
00:51:57,751 --> 00:52:00,021
I've never looked down on or laughed at you.

928
00:52:01,621 --> 00:52:02,621
On the contrary,

929
00:52:04,151 --> 00:52:05,521
I liked you.

930
00:52:10,481 --> 00:52:12,451
What are you talking about?

931
00:52:13,481 --> 00:52:15,951
I was young, and I wasn't allowed to date.

932
00:52:16,721 --> 00:52:18,221
That's why I couldn't tell you.

933
00:52:24,521 --> 00:52:25,521
Is that true?

934
00:53:33,221 --> 00:53:35,021
Get some part-time jobs and go back to school.

935
00:53:35,681 --> 00:53:38,251
I had so much fun in college. I'd love to go back.

936
00:53:39,351 --> 00:53:40,381
I will.

937
00:53:41,621 --> 00:53:43,951
In the end, I saw Young Bin only once from afar.

938
00:53:44,951 --> 00:53:46,651
Still, I'm happy I met you.

939
00:53:49,481 --> 00:53:50,481
Are you?

940
00:53:50,781 --> 00:53:54,381
Thank you for this, too. You're a great guy.

941
00:53:54,651 --> 00:53:56,421
The shirt is not even mine.

942
00:53:56,521 --> 00:53:58,381
It's not only about that.

943
00:53:58,951 --> 00:54:00,351
You really are a great guy.

944
00:54:03,951 --> 00:54:04,951
I'm just...

945
00:54:05,681 --> 00:54:06,751
an unemployed good-for-nothing.

946
00:54:07,381 --> 00:54:08,951
What's wrong about being unemployed?

947
00:54:09,381 --> 00:54:11,981
You're very cheerful and kind.

948
00:54:13,551 --> 00:54:14,881
You're on the same wavelength with me, too.

949
00:54:16,281 --> 00:54:17,381
You look good, too.

950
00:54:18,781 --> 00:54:19,781
I look good?

951
00:54:20,481 --> 00:54:21,621
My goodness.

952
00:54:26,351 --> 00:54:28,581
I'll call you. You can leave now.

953
00:54:29,121 --> 00:54:30,221
My bus will be here soon.

954
00:54:31,751 --> 00:54:33,781
All right. I'll get going.

955
00:54:34,921 --> 00:54:35,921
Make sure...

956
00:54:38,551 --> 00:54:40,181
- to call me. - I will.

957
00:54:40,721 --> 00:54:41,721
Make sure.

958
00:54:42,481 --> 00:54:43,581
- Make sure. - Okay.

959
00:55:09,051 --> 00:55:10,051
What?

960
00:55:12,221 --> 00:55:13,251
What is it now?

961
00:55:13,521 --> 00:55:15,351
Joo Yeon and I are together!

962
00:55:16,351 --> 00:55:17,551
Did you have a dream?

963
00:55:17,821 --> 00:55:19,151
It's true.

964
00:55:19,321 --> 00:55:22,721
She said she had liked me for a long time.

965
00:55:24,451 --> 00:55:27,521
What's with her? Is she pulling your leg?

966
00:55:27,581 --> 00:55:30,821
Are you kidding me? She meant it.

967
00:55:32,151 --> 00:55:34,651
I'm sure she'll regret it.

968
00:55:34,781 --> 00:55:37,321
Hey, you should congratulate me.

969
00:55:37,951 --> 00:55:41,381
Fine, congratulations. Are you sure it's real?

970
00:55:41,881 --> 00:55:43,181
Isn't it some kind of fraud?

971
00:55:43,681 --> 00:55:45,521
Cut it out. Where are you?

972
00:55:45,621 --> 00:55:48,921
I'm seeing Min Ah off at the bus terminal.

973
00:55:49,981 --> 00:55:50,981
What?

974
00:55:51,921 --> 00:55:53,421
Wasn't it going well between you two?

975
00:55:53,781 --> 00:55:55,681
What are you talking about?

976
00:55:56,521 --> 00:55:58,521
Don't try to deny it.

977
00:55:58,651 --> 00:56:01,151
You guys looked like a perfect match.

978
00:56:01,521 --> 00:56:02,681
She's a female version of you.

979
00:56:02,951 --> 00:56:05,151
She's a geek, has no job, and is shameless.

980
00:56:05,321 --> 00:56:06,351
Give it a try.

981
00:56:07,221 --> 00:56:09,881
She seemed to like you, too.

982
00:56:09,951 --> 00:56:12,821
No one likes anyone. You're being ridiculous.

983
00:56:12,951 --> 00:56:15,051
I told you clearly. Don't regret it later.

984
00:56:15,681 --> 00:56:18,151
I should tell Young Bin and Ho Jin, too. Bye.

985
00:56:40,051 --> 00:56:42,481
(Share)

986
00:56:46,451 --> 00:56:47,681
You haven't left?

987
00:56:47,951 --> 00:56:49,621
No, I haven't.

988
00:56:50,251 --> 00:56:52,851
I have something to tell you.

989
00:56:53,681 --> 00:56:55,251
- What is it? - The thing is...

990
00:56:56,351 --> 00:56:59,451
I'm not saying this on the spur of the moment.

991
00:56:59,581 --> 00:57:02,781
I've wanted to say this for a long time.

992
00:57:04,481 --> 00:57:06,551
Were you in the middle of something?

993
00:57:09,021 --> 00:57:10,881
I was posting on social media.

994
00:57:11,451 --> 00:57:12,451
Sorry?

995
00:57:13,251 --> 00:57:16,181
I have a picture of his room. I'm going to sell the shirt.

996
00:57:17,021 --> 00:57:18,181
People will go crazy over it.

997
00:57:19,151 --> 00:57:21,751
Do you have to do it?

998
00:57:22,181 --> 00:57:24,381
Why? It's mine now.

999
00:57:24,851 --> 00:57:26,081
It is,

1000
00:57:26,621 --> 00:57:28,081
but Young Bin's boss...

1001
00:57:28,181 --> 00:57:31,421
swears a lot. He's not a bad person, though.

1002
00:57:31,481 --> 00:57:32,651
There's a guy called Ho Jin, too.

1003
00:57:32,651 --> 00:57:36,151
He's a petty guy. He'll get angry at me.

1004
00:57:36,181 --> 00:57:39,981
Those two will give me a hard time. Please.

1005
00:57:40,751 --> 00:57:43,451
I was going to sell this and come back here next week...

1006
00:57:43,451 --> 00:57:45,051
to get Kim Woo Bin's autograph.

1007
00:57:47,351 --> 00:57:49,981
Do you know him by any chance?

1008
00:57:57,251 --> 00:57:58,251
What's wrong?

1009
00:58:00,651 --> 00:58:01,651
You're so pathetic.

1010
00:58:05,681 --> 00:58:07,151
I thought you were a nice person,

1011
00:58:08,781 --> 00:58:10,851
but you're really pathetic.

1012
00:58:11,281 --> 00:58:15,121
Cut it out. You're even more pathetic. You have no job.

1013
00:58:15,221 --> 00:58:18,521
A moment ago, you said you liked me even though I had no job.

1014
00:58:18,721 --> 00:58:21,021
You said we were on the same wavelength and all.

1015
00:58:21,121 --> 00:58:23,421
You're a stalker who ran away from home.

1016
00:58:23,451 --> 00:58:24,621
You're so immature.

1017
00:58:24,721 --> 00:58:27,621
You're just a good-for-nothing with a celebrity friend.

1018
00:58:27,721 --> 00:58:29,851
Good-for-nothing? You're not even going to school.

1019
00:58:29,951 --> 00:58:32,251
I have part-time jobs. You have nothing.

1020
00:58:33,251 --> 00:58:34,321
That's right.

1021
00:58:36,251 --> 00:58:39,121
- Anyway, I'll take it. - You can't.

1022
00:58:40,521 --> 00:58:43,151
I didn't give it to you so that you could sell it. Give it to me.

1023
00:58:43,251 --> 00:58:45,751
You can't take it back.

1024
00:58:46,921 --> 00:58:49,181
There's a thief!

1025
00:58:49,351 --> 00:58:50,881
He's a thief!

1026
00:58:51,421 --> 00:58:53,151
- You're a thief. - Why am I a thief?

1027
00:58:53,351 --> 00:58:54,681
Don't ever call me.

1028
00:59:11,221 --> 00:59:14,081
Who else is coming than the director?

1029
00:59:15,081 --> 00:59:19,421
Well, I guess the producer will come, too.

1030
00:59:19,781 --> 00:59:20,821
I see.

1031
00:59:24,151 --> 00:59:25,151
By the way,

1032
00:59:25,981 --> 00:59:28,421
I didn't know you'd do this movie.

1033
00:59:29,881 --> 00:59:32,121
You're the one who told me it was good.

1034
00:59:34,621 --> 00:59:36,251
Like you said last time,

1035
00:59:36,781 --> 00:59:39,551
I think I'll trust you.

1036
00:59:40,681 --> 00:59:41,681
I see.

1037
00:59:49,081 --> 00:59:50,251
- Mr. Lee. - Yes.

1038
00:59:55,851 --> 00:59:56,951
The thing is...

1039
00:59:57,851 --> 00:59:59,621
I'll be honest with you.

1040
01:00:00,781 --> 01:00:02,981
It's not a bad movie,

1041
01:00:04,081 --> 01:00:06,851
but I don't think it'd do much good...

1042
01:00:07,621 --> 01:00:09,681
to an actress. It's a small role, too.

1043
01:00:11,551 --> 01:00:14,321
Then why did you tell me to do it?

1044
01:00:14,781 --> 01:00:17,281
It's not appropriate to say it now,

1045
01:00:20,121 --> 01:00:23,721
but I'll tell you the truth. If you take this role,

1046
01:00:24,751 --> 01:00:27,181
it'd help other actors get roles.

1047
01:00:27,921 --> 01:00:29,051
Do you mean Young Bin?

1048
01:00:29,951 --> 01:00:30,951
Yes.

1049
01:00:30,951 --> 01:00:33,081
Are you saying you were using me in the negotiation...

1050
01:00:33,151 --> 01:00:35,881
to get Young Bin a role?

1051
01:00:36,351 --> 01:00:37,481
Yes, I'm sorry.

1052
01:00:44,321 --> 01:00:46,521
You cancel the meeting.

1053
01:00:46,851 --> 01:00:47,851
Okay.

1054
01:00:48,981 --> 01:00:52,081
I'll ask Mr. Kim to find me another manager.

1055
01:00:52,521 --> 01:00:53,521
Well...

1056
01:00:56,921 --> 01:00:58,621
I have nothing to say. I'm sorry.

1057
01:01:03,781 --> 01:01:05,751
What can we do? I knew it'd happen.

1058
01:01:06,251 --> 01:01:07,651
I'm sorry, Mr. Kim.

1059
01:01:08,051 --> 01:01:10,151
It's not your fault. It was my mistake.

1060
01:01:10,981 --> 01:01:13,881
When you said you'd recommend that movie to her,

1061
01:01:14,381 --> 01:01:15,881
I didn't feel comfortable.

1062
01:01:16,851 --> 01:01:17,981
I should have stopped you.

1063
01:01:19,451 --> 01:01:20,921
What should I say to her?

1064
01:01:21,021 --> 01:01:24,251
Should I get her a new car or a bag or something?

1065
01:01:25,521 --> 01:01:27,321
Have you heard anything from Ms. Jo?

1066
01:01:27,321 --> 01:01:29,321
Young Bin even made a cameo appearance.

1067
01:01:29,621 --> 01:01:30,881
The thing is...

1068
01:01:31,621 --> 01:01:32,751
Ms. Jo...

1069
01:01:33,721 --> 01:01:36,251
ordered that Young Bin's scene would get cut out.

1070
01:01:36,551 --> 01:01:39,051
Sorry? Why?

1071
01:01:39,281 --> 01:01:42,151
She got angry that they did it without her permission.

1072
01:01:42,251 --> 01:01:43,821
If it weren't for "Lim Hwa Su", I'd...

1073
01:01:45,321 --> 01:01:46,981
I guess we won't be...

1074
01:01:47,851 --> 01:01:49,321
doing "Lim Hwa Su".

1075
01:01:51,821 --> 01:01:53,651
What should I tell Young Bin?

1076
01:01:54,781 --> 01:01:56,621
I'm sure there's a way.

1077
01:01:56,921 --> 01:01:59,321
Let's talk later. Come to the office first.

1078
01:02:00,881 --> 01:02:01,881
Okay.

1079
01:02:15,881 --> 01:02:16,881
Hello.

1080
01:02:17,381 --> 01:02:19,021
Why did you want to see me?

1081
01:02:19,981 --> 01:02:21,421
Are you divorcing your wife or something?

1082
01:02:21,651 --> 01:02:24,081
We could have met at your office, but you insisted. Come in.

1083
01:02:48,981 --> 01:02:49,981
Well...

1084
01:02:50,921 --> 01:02:53,381
I have a favor to ask.

1085
01:03:12,521 --> 01:03:14,351
Please.

1086
01:03:15,081 --> 01:03:17,651
Young Bin is all I have.

1087
01:03:17,951 --> 01:03:19,951
I beg you.

1088
01:03:20,251 --> 01:03:22,121
- I'll do my best. - Hey.

1089
01:03:23,081 --> 01:03:24,081
Do you...

1090
01:03:25,081 --> 01:03:26,121
have to do this?

1091
01:03:26,321 --> 01:03:28,921
Should I kneel down or something?

1092
01:03:29,221 --> 01:03:30,281
Gosh.

1093
01:03:30,381 --> 01:03:33,981
You can do this. I beg you.

1094
01:03:34,751 --> 01:03:36,251
Please help me.

1095
01:03:36,551 --> 01:03:38,251
- My goodness. - Please.

1096
01:03:38,381 --> 01:03:39,451
Hey.

1097
01:03:48,021 --> 01:03:50,251
Did you ask Ms. Kang?

1098
01:03:50,351 --> 01:03:52,351
I did. We're lovers.

1099
01:03:52,481 --> 01:03:53,781
She's helping me.

1100
01:03:54,581 --> 01:03:55,751
Why are you staring at me?

1101
01:03:55,881 --> 01:03:59,251
He seems to take my joke seriously.

1102
01:03:59,481 --> 01:04:02,221
I wasn't counting on her help. Did you beg her or something?

1103
01:04:02,581 --> 01:04:03,851
Do you think I'd do that?

1104
01:04:06,581 --> 01:04:07,581
Okay.

1105
01:04:15,221 --> 01:04:16,221
Hello.

1106
01:04:24,251 --> 01:04:27,151
I wanted to talk to you in private. Is it okay for you?

1107
01:04:28,381 --> 01:04:29,381
Yes.

1108
01:04:29,881 --> 01:04:32,051
I heard you wanted to see me.

1109
01:04:33,451 --> 01:04:35,021
Yes. I'd like to do "Lim Hwa Su".

1110
01:04:35,951 --> 01:04:37,351
I wanted to apologize, too.

1111
01:04:38,751 --> 01:04:40,181
About "War Terminator",

1112
01:04:41,421 --> 01:04:42,721
I'm really sorry.

1113
01:04:43,421 --> 01:04:46,151
You don't have to do this. I'm not here to hear your apology.

1114
01:04:47,851 --> 01:04:48,851
Then...

1115
01:04:49,181 --> 01:04:50,621
I'm here to turn you down.

1116
01:04:51,351 --> 01:04:55,351
I wanted to tell you that I'm not casting you for "Lim Hwa Su".

1117
01:04:55,681 --> 01:04:57,481
From now on, you don't have to do...

1118
01:04:57,481 --> 01:05:00,351
any interviews or cameo appearances for my movies.

1119
01:05:02,351 --> 01:05:04,221
What can I do for you to stop being angry at me?

1120
01:05:05,151 --> 01:05:08,581
I'm not angry at you. I'm just not going to work with you.

1121
01:05:09,781 --> 01:05:12,021
Can I just do "Lim Hwa Su"?

1122
01:05:12,921 --> 01:05:13,921
No.

1123
01:05:14,621 --> 01:05:16,551
I make movies for a living.

1124
01:05:16,551 --> 01:05:18,821
Movies are important to me. It's my job.

1125
01:05:19,181 --> 01:05:20,721
Everyone involved is important, too.

1126
01:05:21,421 --> 01:05:24,721
You do movies just to meet actresses.

1127
01:05:27,081 --> 01:05:28,521
No, that's not true.

1128
01:05:28,781 --> 01:05:32,651
It is. You do movies so that you can sleep with them.

1129
01:05:32,651 --> 01:05:34,051
Like with An So Hee.

1130
01:05:37,281 --> 01:05:38,281
But...

1131
01:05:38,651 --> 01:05:41,681
should I tell you the real reason why I don't want to work with you?

1132
01:05:43,281 --> 01:05:47,721
I never work with actors who can't act.

1133
01:05:48,451 --> 01:05:51,321
You can't act.

1134
01:05:51,981 --> 01:05:53,351
You're a bad actor.

1135
01:06:05,521 --> 01:06:07,721
Why did she want us to leave?

1136
01:06:08,721 --> 01:06:10,581
I'm so worried I'm craving alcohol.

1137
01:06:10,821 --> 01:06:13,051
Don't worry. It'll be fine.

1138
01:06:19,621 --> 01:06:20,681
Mr. Kim.

1139
01:06:25,321 --> 01:06:27,121
- What? - Well...

1140
01:06:27,981 --> 01:06:29,021
I...

1141
01:06:29,981 --> 01:06:31,481
ended up...

1142
01:06:32,621 --> 01:06:34,821
seeing you beg Ms. Kang.

1143
01:06:36,321 --> 01:06:38,381
Gosh. Did you?

1144
01:06:38,981 --> 01:06:41,251
It's nothing. You just have to swallow your pride...

1145
01:06:41,351 --> 01:06:42,681
and make some compromises.

1146
01:06:43,781 --> 01:06:45,681
Don't tell Young Bin.

1147
01:06:45,881 --> 01:06:47,021
Of course.

1148
01:06:48,981 --> 01:06:50,251
I'm sorry about that.

1149
01:06:50,951 --> 01:06:53,881
You don't have to be. He's my actor.

1150
01:06:55,121 --> 01:06:58,081
You got on bad terms with Lee El because of Young Bin. Work it out.

1151
01:06:58,281 --> 01:06:59,281
I will.

1152
01:07:01,351 --> 01:07:05,051
It was hard to arrange this meeting. I hope it goes well.

1153
01:07:05,151 --> 01:07:06,151
I hope so, too.

1154
01:07:14,151 --> 01:07:16,021
How did it go? Did it go well?

1155
01:07:16,121 --> 01:07:17,221
Why are you out already?

1156
01:07:17,681 --> 01:07:18,721
Are you done already?

1157
01:07:20,081 --> 01:07:21,951
Let's go. I don't think I'll be able to do "Lim Hwa Su".

1158
01:07:22,781 --> 01:07:25,681
What did she say? Did you have a fight?

1159
01:07:28,891 --> 01:07:29,951
You're not answering me.

1160
01:07:30,521 --> 01:07:32,721
Ho Jin, keep him here. I'll go talk to her.

1161
01:07:32,721 --> 01:07:33,721
Okay.

1162
01:07:33,781 --> 01:07:35,721
Stay here. Don't go.

1163
01:07:42,421 --> 01:07:43,481
What happened?

1164
01:07:45,751 --> 01:07:46,751
What is it?

1165
01:07:47,681 --> 01:07:49,921
- I don't want to talk. Let's go. - Wait. What is it?

1166
01:07:50,651 --> 01:07:53,721
Come on. We came all the way here, and what happened?

1167
01:07:55,521 --> 01:07:58,391
You have to tell me.

1168
01:07:59,521 --> 01:08:02,021
Wasn't it you that wanted this meeting?

1169
01:08:02,951 --> 01:08:04,751
I didn't know it'd go like this.

1170
01:08:05,391 --> 01:08:07,681
She wasn't going to work with me.

1171
01:08:07,781 --> 01:08:09,151
She just wanted to take her anger out on me.

1172
01:08:09,521 --> 01:08:11,481
She only talked about "War Terminator".

1173
01:08:11,951 --> 01:08:12,951
Gosh.

1174
01:08:13,581 --> 01:08:14,981
Didn't you expect it?

1175
01:08:15,721 --> 01:08:17,391
Didn't you?

1176
01:08:18,681 --> 01:08:21,891
You wanted the movie desperately. Why didn't you just put up with it?

1177
01:08:23,481 --> 01:08:24,481
Put up with it?

1178
01:08:24,481 --> 01:08:26,621
Yes. You should've just put up with it. Mr. Kim even...

1179
01:08:30,021 --> 01:08:32,681
Mr. Kim went through so much. I had to run here and there, too.

1180
01:08:32,681 --> 01:08:33,751
What's wrong with you?

1181
01:08:34,251 --> 01:08:37,051
You said you'd apologize to her and beg her.

1182
01:08:37,121 --> 01:08:39,281
What are you doing now? You dashed out after a minute.

1183
01:08:39,581 --> 01:08:41,051
I had a good reason.

1184
01:08:41,351 --> 01:08:42,621
You should have put up with it.

1185
01:08:43,521 --> 01:08:45,921
You should have kneeled down and begged her.

1186
01:08:46,221 --> 01:08:47,751
Do you have any idea what I...

1187
01:08:50,391 --> 01:08:51,421
Forget it.

1188
01:08:52,781 --> 01:08:55,451
You quit whenever you feel slightly irritated.

1189
01:08:58,181 --> 01:09:01,151
I'm getting tired of it. We worked so hard in vain.

1190
01:09:01,851 --> 01:09:02,851
Do you think so?

1191
01:09:04,581 --> 01:09:05,581
Then quit.

1192
01:09:10,121 --> 01:09:11,151
I will.

1193
01:09:15,021 --> 01:09:16,021
Get lost.

1194
01:09:16,951 --> 01:09:19,521
- You jerk. - You idiot.

1195
01:09:52,151 --> 01:09:53,651
(Entourage)

1196
01:09:55,321 --> 01:09:57,451
Isn't Ho Jin coming home?

1197
01:09:57,551 --> 01:09:59,681
He told me to quit. I will.

1198
01:09:59,751 --> 01:10:01,421
Do you want me to bring Ho Jin back?

1199
01:10:01,851 --> 01:10:02,951
He's mean.

1200
01:10:03,051 --> 01:10:04,981
He's impatient, stubborn, and short-tempered.

1201
01:10:05,021 --> 01:10:06,321
Did he tell on me like a child?

1202
01:10:06,321 --> 01:10:08,551
- Young Bin thinks... - Does he think I'm irresponsible?

1203
01:10:08,651 --> 01:10:09,851
I just told the truth.

1204
01:10:10,021 --> 01:10:12,821
It's not because he's my actor. If you have eyes, you'd know it!

1205
01:10:13,021 --> 01:10:14,891
You've been working so hard so far!

1206
01:10:15,081 --> 01:10:16,251
I won't see you again.

1207
01:10:16,421 --> 01:10:19,251
What are you doing? Did you decide without telling me?

1208
01:10:20,251 --> 01:10:22,251
I have no reason to go on. It's meaningless.